article.description: Payten Ricks made a 3-pointer with three seconds remaining for Abilene Christian's only lead of the final three minutes and the Wildcats defeated Southeastern Louisiana 75-72 on Saturday.
article.headline: Ricks lifts Abilene Christian over SE Louisiana 75-72
article.linkText: Ricks lifts Abilene Christian over SE Louisiana 75-72
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- Payten Ricks made a 3-pointer with three seconds remaining for Abilene Christian's only lead of the final three minutes and the Wildcats defeated Southeastern Louisiana 75-72 on Saturday. SE Louisiana led 72-70 after a jumper by Moses Greenwood, and Abilene Christian tied it on a layup by Jaren Lewis with 40 seconds remaining. The Wildcats' Damien Daniels came up with a steal with 14 seconds left, and after a timeout, Ricks hit his 3-pointer. Marlain Veal missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer for the Lions. Ricks scored 22 points, making 7 of 8 from the field and all four of his 3-pointers. B.J. Maxwell added 13 points and seven rebounds for Abilene Christian (14-3, 3-1 Southland Conference). Veal had 19 points for SE Louisiana although he went 2 for 12 from the field. He made 15 of 16 free throws. Greenwood added 15 points with 11 rebounds and Keith Charleston had 14 points for the Lions (4-12, 0-3).
